ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Recall context for survey
Notes: e.g., ''Thinking of your entire lifetime'' or ''Since April 1, 2020''

ElementDescription: Form used/assessment name
Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version

ElementDescription: What is the largest number of drinks you can recall ever drinking at any one time?
(ASK IF B_30=99 AND A1=01,99) Would you say five or more, or four or less (is the largest number of drinks ever had at one time)?
Notes: 1 = Five or more; 2 = Four or less; 99 = No answer

ElementDescription: (ASK IF B_30=99 AND A1=02) Would you say five or more, four or more, or less than four drinks (is the largest number of drinks ever had at one time)?
Notes: 1 = Five or more; 2 = Four or less; 3 = Less than four; 99 = No answer

ElementDescription: (ASK IF DRNKSTAT=01,03) About how old were you when you first started drinking alcoholic beverages, not including small tastes?
Notes: 1::90 = Age; 99= No answer; 0= I have never had any alcoholic beverages; 888= No response

ElementDescription: (ASK IF ((B31 <= 19 AND (NOT MISSING)) OR (B31=99)) AND (B_30=5-93 OR B_30=99)) How often did you have five or more drinks on one occasion during your teens? Was it...
Notes: 1 = Every day or nearly every day; 2 = At least once a week; 3 = At least once a month (but less than 1/week); 4 = At least once a year (but less than 1/month); 5 = Less than once a year; 6 = Never; 99 = No answer

ElementDescription: (ASK IF (B32A=04,05,06,99) OR (((B31 <= 19 AND NOT MISSING) OR (B31=99)) AND B_30<5)) Once you began to drink, how often did you drink alcohol during your teens? Was it...
Notes: 1 = Every day or nearly every day; 2 = At least once a week; 3 = At least once a month (but less than 1/week); 4 = At least once a year (but less than 1/month); 5 = Less often than that; 99 = No answer
